author: Annie Martin
title: St. Vincent waitresses at Dallas taco restaurant
text:
DALLAS, Oct. 12 (UPI) -- Singer Annie Clark, aka St. Vincent, surprised fans by waiting tables at her sister's restaurant, Resident Tacqueria, in Dallas, Texas, over the weekend.
The 33-year-old musician served tables at the establishment's soft opening last week, and St. Vincent came in to help the owner -- her sister, Amy Savoie.
"She was just doing it as an excellent sister and knew we needed the help," Savoie told E! News . "The restaurant was super busy and it was fantastic to have such a great reaction from the neighborhood about the restaurant."
Several people recognized the "Digital Witness" singer and posted about the sighting on social media. "Hungry? Thirsty? When do u [sic] ever get to have Annie bring u the best tacos and margaritas to your table!" one such fan wrote on Instagram.
Annie Clark, aka St. Vincent, waited tables at Resident Taqueria over the weekend. Instagram /kotokotooto St. Vincent was born in Tulsa, Okla., in September 1982, and is one of eight siblings. She released her fourth studio album, St. Vincent , in February 2014, which won Best Alternative Music Album at the 2015 Grammy Awards. She is also known for her relationship with English model Cara Delevingne .
